                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Quote Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;While an Opportunity in Salesforce is a potential deal, a Quote contains the products that are a part of that deal. A Quote is also what is turned into a PDF and shared with a customer. One great Salesforce feature is that an Opportunity can have multiple Quotes. So, for example, if you wish to present a district with three different options, you can create three different Quotes within the same Opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Important Note: Although you can create multiple Quotes, only one at a time can be active, or &apos;synced&apos; to the Opportunity. The cost of the synced Quote will show up as the Opportunity&apos;s amount, and the synced Quote&apos;s Products will be shown as the Opportunity&apos;s Products.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;To sync a Quote to its related Opportunity, click on the &apos;Start Sync&apos; button in the upper right-hand corner on this page. Alternatively, click &apos;Stop Sync&apos; to stop the current quote from syncing with it&apos;s Opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://web.microsoftstream.com/video/b6f57171-b60f-41dc-bc5f-a572cd802add&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Quotes Screencast&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
